When God's nearness takes possession of a man's heart, it overwhelms all else,
both the inward infiltrations of the purposes and the outward motions of the
members. Thereafter that man continues, going or coming, taking or givingï¼š
there prevails in him the purpose which has ruled his mind, namely, the love of
God and His nearness.
